  "text": "Garmin Epix Gen 2 $485 $900 Save $415 With its big, bold AMOLED display and plenty of power under the hood, the Garmin Epix Gen 2 is built for folks who take their health tracking seriously. From heart rate to sleep to stress, it keeps tabs on it all—and right now, it’s going for one of its best prices on Amazon. Garmin has been in the wearables market long enough to know what people actually need—whether you're just lacing up for your first run or you're the type who signs up for ultramarathons. It's got a watch for every kind of grind, and the Epix Gen 2 is a real standout. It’s the kind of watch that pulls double duty—loaded with serious athletic features while still looking sleek enough to rock every day, whether you're hitting the gym or heading out for the night. Right now, you can grab the white titanium Garmin Epix Gen 2 on Amazon for just $485, way down from its usual $900. That’s a massive $415 off, or about 46% shaved off the price tag. Why the Garmin Epix Gen 2 is worth your money Even though it’s not the newest kid on the block, the Garmin Epix Gen 2 has been getting steady software updates since launch, so it’s still packed with all the essentials Garmin is known for. This thing is built tough, too. It’s got a titanium bezel that looks sharp and adds protection without weighing you down, and the main body is made from fiber-reinforced polymer, meaning it's light, strong, and ready to take a hit. Related The Epix Gen 2 packs a bright 1.3-inch AMOLED screen that’s always ready when you glance down—and it’s tough, too, thanks to a sapphire crystal lens that laughs off scratches. It's sealed tight and water-ready, rated for up to 10 ATM. So whether you're caught in the rain, hitting the pool, or out on the water, it's built to keep up without blinking. Sure, the shiny new Garmin Fenix 8 might be Garmin’s latest and greatest smartwatch, but the Epix Gen 2 still hits hard, especially at its current sale price. You’re getting serious bang for your 