03cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe Epix Gen 2 packs a bright 1.3-inch AMOLED screen that’s always ready when you glance down—and it’s tough, too, thanks to a sapphire crystal lens that laughs off scratches. It\u0026#39;s sealed tight and water-ready, rated for up to 10 ATM. So whether you\u0026#39;re caught in the rain, hitting the pool, or out on the water, it\u0026#39;s built to keep up without blinking.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eSure, the shiny new \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/garmin-fenix-8-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eGarmin Fenix 8\u003c/a\u003e might be \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/best-garmin-smartwatch/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eGarmin’s latest and greatest smartwatch\u003c/a\u003e, but the Epix Gen 2 still hits hard, especially at its current sale price. You’re getting serious bang for your buck here. With the Fenix 8 starting at $1,099, the Epix Gen 2 is a smart pick if you want top-tier features without the top-tier price. It’s loaded with all the essentials—GPS tracking, training tools, maps, you name it—and it doesn’t skimp on the smart stuff either, like built-in music storage and NFC payments.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cul\u003e\n                                    \u003cli\u003e\n                    \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/wearables/\" title=\"Smartwatches \u0026amp; Wearables\"\u003e\n                                                                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://static0.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/google-pixel-watch-3-1.jpg?q=50\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=32\u0026amp;h=32\u0026amp;dpr=1.5\" alt=\"Smartwatches \u0026amp; Wearables\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"/\u003e\n                        \u003c/p\